  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The models developed in this work are designed to predict only one phase at a time.",
    "To handle multi-phase mixtures, we use an algorithm that iterates between the identification of constituent phases and the subtraction of their associated diffraction peaks.",
    "Further details on this algorithm can be found in previous work 19.",
    "Because PDFs contain many diffuse and overlapping features, they are not well-suited for peak subtraction algorithms.",
    "Therefore, when classifying multi-phase mixtures using the PDF-trained model, we iteratively convert the data back and forth between 2θ and Q-space."
  ],
